selector_to_html = {"a[href=\"#applying-distance-restraints-in-classical-md-simulations\"]": "<h1 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Applying Distance Restraints in Classical MD SImulations<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#applying-distance-restraints-in-classical-md-simulations\" title=\"Permalink to this heading\">#</a></h1><p>We can apply restraints to atoms or residues if we are interested in modelling a specific process such as diffusion or binding.</p><p>Buiding on from the <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">simple</span></code> tutorial, the goal here is to simulate the process of 2 Alanine Dipeptide molecules slowly diffusing away from each other using <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">sander</span></code> in the <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">ambertools</span></code> conda environment.</p>", "a[href=\"#visualize-and-analysis\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Visualize and Analysis<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#visualize-and-analysis\" title=\"Permalink to this heading\">#</a></h2><p>Now you can visual the results with VMD or Chimera, and perform some analysis.</p>", "a[href=\"#prepare-files-folders\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Prepare Files &amp; Folders<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#prepare-files-folders\" title=\"Permalink to this heading\">#</a></h2><p>Make a project folder, called \u201cdistance\u201d in the <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">~/Tutorials</span></code> directory, and change to that directory. <em>Optionally, if you downloaded the reference file, we will move <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">distance.tar.bz2</span></code> into the reference folder.</em></p>", "a[href=\"#make-topology-and-coordinate-files\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Make Topology and Coordinate Files<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#make-topology-and-coordinate-files\" title=\"Permalink to this heading\">#</a></h2><p>Similar to the <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">simple</span></code> tutorial. We use <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">leap</span></code> to prepare our Amber topology and coordinate file. Since Alanine Dipeptide is still an amino acid, we can use <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">tleap</span></code> to generate the topology (<code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">.parm7</span></code>) and coordinate files(<code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">.rst7</span></code>). The <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">tleap</span></code> program contains reference coordinates for standard residues to generate  missing atoms, this function is base on the residue name.</p><p>Give <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">tleap</span></code> instructions by making a file called \u201c<a class=\"reference external\" href=\"http://tleap.in\">tleap.in</a>\u201d containing:</p>", "a[href=\"#restraint-files\"]": "<h3 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Restraint Files<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#restraint-files\" title=\"Permalink to this heading\">#</a></h3><p>To apply a distance restraint, I typically use the Umbrella Sampling approach. If I avoid all the gritty details, the setup only requires 1 additional restraint file (<code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">cv.rst</span></code>) for each restraint value.</p><p>If our initial distance between the 2 molecules is 5 \u00c5, and the goal is to observe some property of the system when the distance is 15 \u00c5. Then I want to sample some distances &lt; 5 \u00c5 and increment that distance at some value until I reach 15 \u00c5. The increment between distance will depend on the system and property you\u2019re studying.</p>", "a[href=\"#run-md-with-bash-script\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Run MD with Bash Script<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#run-md-with-bash-script\" title=\"Permalink to this heading\">#</a></h2><p>Instead of running each simulation one command at a time (like we did in the <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">simple</span></code> tutorial), we can write a script to run it for us! Make a file called, <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">vi</span> <span class=\"pre\">runmd.sh</span></code> with:</p>", "a[href=\"#prepare-md-inputs-simulation-settings\"]": "<h2 class=\"tippy-header\" style=\"margin-top: 0;\">Prepare MD Inputs - Simulation Settings<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#prepare-md-inputs-simulation-settings\" title=\"Permalink to this heading\">#</a></h2><p>Prepare 2 MD input files, <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">min.mdin</span></code>, and <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">heat.mdin</span></code>. These files contain the settings for the first stage of the simulations.</p>", "a[href=\"#id1\"]": "<figure class=\"align-default\" id=\"id1\">\n<a class=\"reference internal image-reference\" href=\"../../_images/distance.mov\"><img alt=\"../../_images/distance.mov\" src=\"../../_images/distance.mov\" style=\"width: 50%;\"/></a>\n<figcaption>\n<p><span class=\"caption-number\">Fig. 2 </span><span class=\"caption-text\">MD trajectories of 2 Alanine Dipeptide molecules (<em>shown as ball-and-stick</em>), solvated in water (<em>shown as line</em>) as viewed on VMD. Resrtrains were placed on the center-of-mass between both molecules starting from a distance of 4 \u00c5 and gradually increased to 15 \u00c5.</span><a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#id1\" title=\"Permalink to this image\">#</a></p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>"}
skip_classes = ["headerlink", "sd-stretched-link"]

window.onload = function () {
    for (const [select, tip_html] of Object.entries(selector_to_html)) {
        const links = document.querySelectorAll(` ${select}`);
        for (const link of links) {
            if (skip_classes.some(c => link.classList.contains(c))) {
                continue;
            }

            tippy(link, {
                content: tip_html,
                allowHTML: true,
                arrow: true,
                placement: 'auto-start', maxWidth: 500, interactive: false,

            });
        };
    };
    console.log("tippy tips loaded!");
};
